explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach to find the concatenated substrings. It first builds a map to store the frequency of each word in the given array. Then it iterates over the string and for each substring of length equal to the total length of all words, it checks if the frequency of each word in the substring matches the frequency in the map. If it does, it adds the starting index of the substring to the result list.

